# Curated, advisory clang-tidy configuration (Phase 5 Task 7).
#
# Advisory only: WarningsAsErrors is empty and the CI job that runs this
# config uses continue-on-error: true. Nothing here gates a merge; it is a
# tuned "what to look at" signal for changed files.
#
# Starting point (per the Phase 5 plan) was:
#   bugprone-*, performance-*, modernize-use-nullptr, modernize-use-override,
#   modernize-loop-convert, minus bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters and
#   bugprone-narrowing-conversions.
# That was run over three representative files (src/fight.cpp — hot combat
# path/live melee loop; src/character_json.cpp — Phase 2a JSON persistence;
# src/comm.cpp — networking/descriptor handling) against the macos-arm64
# compile database (build/macos-arm64/compile_commands.json). The trial
# surfaced three checks whose signal-to-noise ratio is bad specifically for
# this codebase's idioms, so they were tuned out below (each documented
# where it is disabled). Every other default-enabled check in the two
# groups produced real, low-volume, actionable findings (nullptr literals,
# missing `override`, CRTP accessibility, signed-char narrowing, etc.) and
# was left enabled.
Checks: >
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  modernize-use-nullptr,
  modernize-use-override,
  modernize-loop-convert,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-narrowing-conversions,
  -bugprone-macro-parentheses,
  -bugprone-assignment-in-if-condition,
  -performance-enum-size

# Disabled-check rationale (one entry per '-check' above beyond the two the
# plan named up front):
#
# -bugprone-macro-parentheses
#   By far the loudest single check in the trial: ~204 hits across the 3
#   trial files alone (mostly `#define FOO -1`-style constant macros and
#   backslash-continued function-like macros in headers like structs.h,
#   spells.h, interpre.h). This codebase is soaked in that classic-C macro
#   idiom (hundreds of unparenthesized constant/flag macros predating this
#   project). Wrapping them all in parens is a huge, purely-mechanical,
#   effectively repo-wide diff for near-zero real bug yield here — none of
#   the sampled hits were an actual latent bug, just the idiom. Left
#   disabled to keep the advisory signal readable; worth revisiting only as
#   a dedicated, scoped cleanup task, not as background CI noise.
#
# -bugprone-assignment-in-if-condition
#   ~9 hits across the 3 trial files, all of the form
#   `if (!(ptr = some_call()))` / `if ((x = f()) == 0)` — the deliberate,
#   long-standing K&R/CircleMUD-lineage idiom this codebase uses everywhere
#   for "call and null/zero-check in one line" (comm.cpp's descriptor and
#   input-parsing code is full of it). The check does not special-case the
#   already-parenthesized/explicit-comparison forms this codebase
#   consistently uses to signal intent, so it would fire on essentially
#   every instance of an established idiom rather than catching accidental
#   `=`-for-`==` typos. Disabled as idiom noise, not a correctness gap.
#
# -performance-enum-size
#   7 hits per trial file (the same handful of header enums re-flagged in
#   every translation unit), suggesting shrinking each enum's underlying
#   type to uint8_t/int8_t. None of the specific enums flagged in the trial
#   was verified to sit inside a persisted struct — of those checked, some
#   are dead or unreferenced, some are transient in-memory state, and one is
#   derived by cast from an int field rather than stored. The disable is a
#   conservative policy call, not a per-enum finding: this codebase persists
#   game data through explicit-offset legacy binary converters and pins
#   struct-layout-sensitive behavior with byte-identical goldens
#   (docs/data-formats/*, the 32-bit-only legacy_*_fixture.bin fixtures)
#   across a four-ABI compile matrix, so ANY game-data enum MAY back a
#   layout-sensitive struct, and acting on this check safely would require
#   a per-enum persistence/ABI audit first. That audit is out of scope for
#   an advisory-only lint config, and the payoff (a few bytes on values
#   never allocated in bulk) doesn't justify running with the check enabled
#   and triaging each hit ad hoc. Disabled until such an audit exists.

WarningsAsErrors: ''
HeaderFilterRegex: '^.*/src/.*'
